The paper proposes a scalable randomized block coordinate Frank-Wolfe algorithm for convex optimization with general compact convex constraints, which has diverse applications in analyzing biomedical data for better understanding cellular and disease mechanisms. The paper focuses on implementing the derived stochastic block coordinate algorithm to align protein-protein interaction networks for identifying conserved functional pathways based on the IsoRank framework. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
